text: “I think no matter how much time passes by, I will always have a weak spot for you. And that terrifies the hell out of me.
“In order to move on, you must understand why you felt what you did and why you no longer need to feel it.
“One day, you and I are gonna wake up and be alright. Maybe not today, maybe not tomorrow but one day. One day. I promise you.
“When someone is in your heart, they’re never truly gone. They can come back to you, even at unlikely times.
"She put me back together so well that I forgot I was broken.
“Sometimes the most ordinary things can be made extraordinary by doing them with the right people.
“Never apologize for burning too brightly or collapsing into yourself every night. That is how galaxies are made.
“These pains you feel are messengers. Listen to them.
“I want to write a novel about silence. The things people don’t say.
“Soon I’ll grow up, and I won’t even flinch at your name.
“I hope you will go out and let stories happen to you.
"It's always nice being wanted. Even if it's by the wrong person.
“Don’t ever think I fell for you, or fell over you. I didn’t fall in love, I rose in it. I saw you and made up my mind.
“I feel like a part of my soul has loved you since the beginning of everything. Maybe we’re from the same star.
“It feels like I am thinking too much about what I should do next to improve my path through life, instead of doing it.
“That is the saddest part when you lose someone you love—that person keeps changing. And later you wonder, is this the same person I lost?
“You know you really love someone, when you don’t hate them for breaking your heart.
"There are a million ways to bleed. But you are by far my favourite.
“Make yourself a priority. At the end of the day, you’re your longest commitment.

"Your poetry is lonely. And yet, you write to feel less alone.
“There’s a special place in my heart for the ones who were with me at my lowest and still loved me when I wasn’t very loveable.
“Memories are dangerous things. You turn them over and over, until you know every touch and corner, still, you’ll find an edge to cut you.
“One of the most beautiful qualities of true friendship is to understand and to be understood.
"She put me back together so well that I forgot I was broken.
"My nights are for overthinking, my mornings are for oversleeping.

“Be silly. Be honest. Be kind.
“I hope you look for me in everyone you meet.

“I don’t want to be a sweetheart. I want to be the fucking love of your life.

"Once, years ago, I looked up by mistake and fell into your eyes.
I’m still falling. Sometimes, it feels like flying.
"Somewhere, someone knows the words to the songs you sing.
“If you remember me, then I don't care if everyone else forgets.
"I take great care of myself by carefully shutting myself away.
“I don’t think this generation will ever understand the language of love letters.
“Wherever you go, go with all your heart.
“But I tried, didn’t I? Goddamnit, at least I did that.
“The loneliest moment in someone’s life is when they are watching their whole world fall apart, and all they can do is stare blankly.
"When they are gone, you will remember every single opportunity you had to speak them. And didn't.
“That's what careless words do. They make people love you a little less.
“One of the hardest decisions you’ll ever face in life is choosing whether to walk away or try harder.
“Good relationships don’t just happen. They take time, patience, and two people who truly want to be together.
“But the heart has its own memory and I have forgotten nothing.
“Why is it that some secrets can drown you while some pull you close to others in a way you never want to lose?
"The worst lies are the lies we tell ourselves.
“I understand that nobody understands me, but I can’t be someone I’m not.
"And then my soul saw you and it kind of went "Oh there you are. I've been looking for you.
“I’ll marry a person who knows how I take my tea, coffee, and alcohol, and knows when to make which.
“Don't you think it would be wonderful to get rid of everything and everybody and just go some place where you don't know a soul?
“Don’t set yourself on fire to keep others warm.
"I'm not scared of never meeting you. I'm scared of having met you, and let you go.
“I want to write a novel about silence. The things people don’t say.
"Yes, I'm drunk. And you're beautiful. And tomorrow morning, I'll be sober but you'll still be beautiful.
“I always knew looking back on the tears would make me laugh, but I never knew looking back on the laughs would make me cry.
"Write her a letter, send her a flower, love only gets old if you let it.
“I myself am made entirely of flaws, stitched together with good intentions.
“You’re scared of the way I make you feel because you don’t want to feel anything.
“The most selfless thing I’ve ever done was fight the urge to ask you to stay.
“One of the hardest decisions you’ll ever face in life is choosing whether to walk away or try harder.
“You are so brave and quiet, I forget you are suffering.
“No matter how honestly you open up to someone, there are still things you cannot reveal.
“Every woman wants a man who'll fall in love with her soul as well as her body.
“Each time I did something to push him away, I was terrified it would work.
“Maybe a soulmate is someone who understands the very deepest parts of you without you having to explain.

“I’ll never ask you
to be anything other
than exactly you.
“But someday I’m going to find somebody and love him and love him and never let him go.
“The more I threw away, the more I found.
“Everything has changed and yet, I am more me than I’ve ever been.
“It is a frightening thought, that in one fraction of a moment you can fall in the kind of love that takes a lifetime to get over.
“I’m tired. Tired today, tired tomorrow. I was tired yesterday and am tired today.
“Loneliness: there is no organ that can take it all.
